Plugin Step: Parse Pattern Type

User spicifies source directory of pattern type file

This step will parse pattern name and version information from the source.

Plugin Step: Import Pattern Type

User spicifies cloud type, base directory for command line tool, the hostname of the cloud provider, 
user name and password to access the cloud provider, and pattern type source directory.

This step will import the pattern type to the cloud provider. 

Plugin Step: Accept Licenses of Pattern Type

User spicifies pattern type and version, cloud type, base directory for command line tool, the hostname of the cloud provider, 
user name and password to access the cloud provider.

This step will accept the license for the pattern type. 

Plugin Step: Enable Pattern Type

User spicifies pattern type and version, cloud type, base directory for command line tool, the hostname of the cloud provider, 
user name and password to access the cloud provider.

This step will enable the pattern type.

Plugin Step: Delete Pattern Type

User spicifies pattern type and version, cloud type, base directory for command line tool, the hostname of the cloud provider, 
user name and password to access the cloud provider.

This step will delete the pattern type.  

Plugin Step: Deploy Shared Service

User spicifies shared service name and version, public key, deployment parameters file, cloud type, base directory for command line tool, the hostname of the cloud provider, 
user name and password to access the cloud provider, cloud group, cloud ip group, cloud environment profile.

This step will deploy the shared service.